text: Really nice Penang Char Kway Teow and Prawn Mee. Teh O cost $1.40. Overall nice place to have bf.

Super expensive coffee. One cup of Kopi O is a whopping $1.40.

Hokkien mee stall has changed owner. Similar taste but not the same.

Zichar is on the pricey side.

The gentleman from Vietnam makes v good chicken chop. Tried a few time and the consistency is good. V confident cook! Ask me to smell his cooking nice or not. I like!
Coffeeshop don’t open on Sunday.

Must try the 梹城抄棵条！You don’t need to go Malaysia to get the taste.  The only problem may be the road side car park. Next , open air the old coffee shop where you can’t find in the housing estate or shopping mall 😃😃😃😃😃
Had fried hokkien mee ($5) for lunch on 13/3/23, was good
